<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Choose a tunnel height that clears your crop at full size while still allowing you to seal the edges securely. For most raised beds, this means a moderate height that balances growth space with effective pest exclusion.
  </p>

  <p>
    Avoid going too low or too high, and adjust based on crop type and conditions.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Just enough height is better than too much or too little.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    The best insect netting height for raised bed tunnels is one that provides enough clearance for plant growth while maintaining a secure barrier against pests.
  </p>

  <p>
    Matching height to crop size and conditions helps create a more effective and manageable setup.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
